y-erdogan-inflation.html','Fri, 02 Jun 2023 14:59:26 +0000'),(11,3,1832,'New World Bank President Ajay Banga Leads at a Pivotal Moment','The incoming president will be under pressure to juggle the global institution’s ambitions to combat climate change and fight poverty.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/02/business/economy/ajay-banga-world-bank.html','Fri, 02 Jun 2023 14:50:16 +0000'),(11,3,1833,'Biden Praises Debt-Ceiling Deal in Address to the Nation','The president addressed the nation from the Oval Office on Friday evening, after congressional passage of legislation to prevent economic calamity.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/02/us/politics/biden-debt.html','Sat, 03 Jun 2023 00:49:04 +0000'),(11,3,1834,'Why May’s Jobs Data Complicates Inflation Picture for the Fed','Federal Reserve officials are expected to leave rates unchanged at their June 13-14 meeting. Fresh jobs data might make the choice harder.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/02/business/economy/federal-reserve-jobs-interest-rates.html','Fri, 02 Jun 2023 20:12:18 +0000'),(11,3,1835,'U.S. Added 339,000 Jobs in May Despite Economic Clouds','Employers added 339,000 workers in May, the Labor Department said, though the report also offered signs of shakiness.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/02/business/economy/jobs-report-may-2023.html','Fri, 02 Jun 2023 20:14:43 +0000'),(11,3,1836,'How to Enforce a Debt Deal: Through ‘Meat-Ax’ Cuts Nobody Wants','The debt-limit legislation includes a provision meant to force both sides to pass additional bills following through on their deal: the threat of automatic cuts if they fail to do so.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/01/us/politics/debt-limit-spending-cuts.html','Fri, 02 Jun 2023 03:21:00 +0000'),(11,3,1837,'Supreme Court Backs Employer in Suit Over Strike Losses','The justices ruled that federal labor law did not block state courts from ruling on a case regarding damage caused when workers walked off the job.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/01/business/economy/supreme-court-strikes-teamsters.html','Thu, 01 Jun 2023 20:29:51 +0000'),(11,3,1838,'Job Openings Rose in April, Defying Cooling Trend','The Labor Department report may put pressure on the Federal Reserve to raise interest rates further to stem inflation.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/31/business/economy/jobs-layoffs-openings-jolts.html','Wed, 31 May 2023 19:34:44 +0000'),(11,3,1839,'Ireland Worries That Brexit Will Ruin Fishing Industry','Along Ireland’s coast, fishing has been a way of life for generations. But changes to the industry — including a cut in quotas after Brexit and a government plan to scrap boats — may see a way of life disappear.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/31/world/europe/ireland-fishing-quotas-decommissioning.html','Thu, 01 Jun 2023 11:09:03 +0000'),(11,3,1840,'Remote Work Gives Amazon Workers a Common Cause','At Amazon, warehouse workers have shown support for corporate colleagues, noting they have nothing to gain if office workers lose flexibility that the pandemic proved possible.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/31/business/work-home-return-office-amazon.html','Wed, 31 May 2023 22:40:24 +0000'),(11,3,1841,'House Passes Debt Ceiling Bill in Bipartisan Vote to Avert Default','An overwhelming bipartisan coalition pushed through the compromise struck by Speaker Kevin McCarthy and President Biden, even as lawmakers in both parties signaled displeasure with the plan.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/31/us/politics/debt-ceiling-house-vote.html','Fri, 02 Jun 2023 04:08:16 +0000'),(11,3,1842,'Debt Ceiling Deal Would Reinstate Student Loan Payments','The legislation would prevent President Biden from issuing another last-minute extension on the payments beyond the end of the summer.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/30/us/politics/student-loan-payments-biden-debt.html','Thu, 01 Jun 2023 03:04:12 +0000'),(11,3,1843,'Companies Push Prices Higher, Protecting Profits but Adding to Inflation','Corporate profits have been bolstered by higher prices even as some of the costs of doing business have fallen in recent months.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/30/business/economy/inflation-companies-profits-higher-prices.html','Wed, 31 May 2023 22:29:51 +0000'),(11,3,1844,'Here’s What’s in the Debt Ceiling Deal','Two years of spending caps, additional work requirements for food stamps and cuts to I.R.S. funding are among the components in the deal.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/29/us/politics/debt-ceiling-agreement.html','Fri, 02 Jun 2023 04:08:39 +0000'),(11,3,1845,'Why the Debt Limit Spending Cuts Likely Won’t Shake the Economy','With low unemployment and above-trend inflation, the economy is well positioned to absorb the modest budget cuts that President Biden and Republicans negotiated.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/29/us/politics/debt-ceiling-economy.html','Mon, 29 May 2023 09:26:04 +0000'),(11,3,1846,'Biden Officials Announce Indo-Pacific Trade Deal, Clashing With Industry Groups','The United States announced a deal to coordinate supply chains with allies, but prominent business groups said the deal fell short on reducing tariffs and other trade barriers.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/27/business/economy/biden-indo-pacific-trade-deal.html','Sat, 27 May 2023 20:06:37 +0000'),(11,3,1847,'Yellen’s Debt Limit Warnings Went Unheeded, Leaving Her to Face Fallout','The Treasury secretary, who considered ways to contain the fallout of a default when she was a Fed official in 2011, had urged Democrats to raise the limit while they still had control of Congress.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/27/us/politics/yellen-debt-limit.html','Sun, 28 May 2023 00:52:56 +0000'),(11,3,1848,'Time Is Running Out for Congress to Raise the Debt Ceiling','With a June 5 deadline looming, there is much to be done to prevent the default that leaders of both parties said would never happen.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/05/26/us/politics/debt-limit-default-mccarthy-mcconnell-biden-congress.html','Fri, 26 May 2023 22:17:39 +0000'),(11,4,1849,'Apple Debuts the Vision Pro, Its VR Headset, at WWDC 2023','The device, called Vision Pro and shaped like a pair of ski goggles, faces a skeptical consumer market and competition from others, like fellow tech giant Meta.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/05/technology/apple-headset-virtual-reality-wwdc.html','Mon, 05 Jun 2023 20:50:02 +0000'),(11,4,1850,'Twitter’s U.S. Ad Sales Plunge 59% as Woes Continue','In internal forecasts, the company projected that ad sales would keep declining, handing a tough challenge to its new chief executive.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/05/technology/twitter-ad-sales-musk.html','Mon, 05 Jun 2023 20:10:22 +0000'),(11,4,1851,'These Activists Distrust Voting Machines. Just Don’t Call Them Election Deniers.','As election activists rally against new voting machines, they are drifting into territory now dominated by conspiracy theorists.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/04/technology/voting-machines-election-deniers.html','Sun, 04 Jun 2023 09:00:38 +0000'),(11,4,1852,'How to Use AI to Edit and Generate Stunning Photos','An A.I.-powered version of  Photoshop and the image generator Midjourney live up to the hype.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/02/technology/ai-photo-editing.html','Mon, 05 Jun 2023 08:26:31 +0000'),(11,4,1853,'Robert Kennedy Jr., With Musk, Pushes Right-Wing Ideas and Misinformation','Mr. Kennedy, a long-shot Democratic presidential candidate with surprisingly high polling numbers, said he wanted to close the Mexican border and attributed the rise of mass shootings to pharmaceutical drugs.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/05/us/politics/robert-f-kennedy-jr-twitter-2024.html','Mon, 05 Jun 2023 22:10:26 +0000'),(11,4,1854,'Los mejores ‘prompts’ para ChatGPT','Nuestro columnista de tecnología personal comparte cómo mejorar muchas partes de tu vida.','https://www.nytimes.com/es/2023/06/05/espanol/mejores-prompts-ia.html','Mon, 05 Jun 2023 09:00:07 +0000'),(11,4,1855,'Don Bateman, Trailblazer in